news.title: Brigade Enterprises' net profit up 47.97% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Brigade Enterprises reported a significant 47.97% surge in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹170.28 crore. Total income also grew by 25.63% to ₹1,429.86 crore, driven by strong performance in real estate, leasing, and hospitality segments. The company also announced the appointment of Debashis Chatterjee as an additional director.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to jointly develop residential project in Vadodara
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces has launched a joint development project on Ajwa Road in Vadodara, marking its entry into the city's residential market. This project boasts a top-line potential exceeding ₹700 crore. The company plans further expansion into Gujarat, Bengaluru, and the Mumbai Metropolitan Region this year.

news.title: ANP Privado: Where luxury finds its privacy in the heart of Baner
news.para: ANP Corp, with nearly three decades of real estate experience, unveils ANP Privado, a 10-acre luxury enclave in Baner, Pune. This development offers 3, 4 & 5 BHK residences with over 80% open spaces and a 50,000 sq. ft. clubhouse featuring over 65 amenities.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to launch citywide AI-based property survey after nine years
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation is launching a citywide property survey using AI after a nine-year gap to correct tax assessment discrepancies and boost revenue. A pilot project successfully identified new and modified properties, confirming AI's accuracy in capturing on-ground changes. This initiative aims to update records, ensure fairer assessments, and recover significant tax arrears.

news.title: HYDRAA clears encroachments in Hastinapuram & Chandanagar
news.para: Hyderabad Disaster Management and Asset Protection Agency (HYDRAA) has cleared encroachments from government and community land in Hastinapuram and Gangaram Colony. Acting on public complaints via the Prajavani platform, HYDRAA removed illegal constructions from a park area and a plot designated for public amenities. Fencing and protective boards were installed to secure the cleared lands.

news.title: About 30,000 houses provided to people of Nagaland under PMAY-Urban
news.para: Nagaland has achieved a remarkable 96% completion rate for nearly 30,000 houses under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Urban (PMAY-U). The scheme's second phase, PMAY-U 2.0, launched with the Angikaar campaign, aims to accelerate implementation through public outreach. The enhanced subsidy for affordable housing has been increased to Rs 2.5 lakh.

news.title: Experion Developers awards ₹800 crore construction contract to TATA Projects
news.para: Experion Developers has appointed TATA Projects as the principal contractor for its ₹800 crore residential project, The Trillion, in Gurugram. This 2.5 million sq ft development will feature 45-floor towers, representing a significant investment of ₹2,500 crore and aiming to set a benchmark in high-rise living.

news.title: Pune: Trust too willing to cancel Model Colony land deal, status quo till October 30
news.para: The Seth Hirachand Nemchand Digambar Jain Boarding Trust trustees have agreed to cancel a controversial land deal. This follows developer Vishal Gokhale's withdrawal from the agreement. The trustees informed the charity commissioner of their decision. They cited community harmony and trust reputation as reasons. A Jain temple on the property was a key concern.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji plans to raise ₹22,000-crore in early 2026 to retire high-cost debt
news.para: Shapoorji Pallonji Group plans to raise $2.5 billion next year to retire high-cost debt. The infrastructure conglomerate is contacting existing investors to gauge their repayment preferences, aiming to refinance $1.7 billion of existing debt. This move is part of a capital restructuring for group entity Goswami Infratech.

news.title: E-khata now mandatory for obtaining A-khata in Bengaluru
news.para: Bengaluru's B-khata property owners face a new e-khata prerequisite for conversion to A-khata, starting November 1. This digital step, alongside a 5% fee and other charges, has frustrated citizens. Officials defend the move as crucial for verifying ownership and preventing corruption, aiming to boost tax compliance and infrastructure development.

news.title: Gstaad Hotels likely to raise ₹1,300 crore from sale of JW Marriott Bengaluru
news.para: Gstaad Hotels is poised to generate ₹1,300 crore by offloading the JW Marriott Bengaluru, a notable event in the Indian hotel market. With more than 40 entities, ranging from corporate giants to private equity investors, expressing interest, this sale is part of Gstaad's efforts to navigate through bankruptcy.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing board lists 4,200 units for home buyers in Lucknow
news.para: Uttar Pradesh housing authorities are streamlining property acquisition by creating a centralized list of vacant residential units. Potential buyers can now view property details, including photographs and geo-coordinates, on individual and departmental portals. This initiative aims to simplify the process, allowing interested individuals to register and participate in lottery draws for government-backed housing schemes.

news.title: Landowners in JDAs not ‘aggrieved persons’ under RERA: Tribunal clears legal grey area
news.para: Telangana RERA Appellate Tribunal ruled landowners in joint development agreements are not 'allottees' and cannot seek redressal against developers. The tribunal clarified that basic project details on a company website or display boards at a site do not constitute illegal advertising before registration. This decision settles a key ambiguity regarding landowners' rights under RERA.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh govt extends layout regularisation scheme deadline by three months
news.para: The Andhra Pradesh government has extended the deadline for its Layout Regularisation Scheme (LRS) by three months, until January 23, 2026, due to a poor response. This move aims to bring unauthorized layouts and plots under the planning framework and ensure urban growth.

news.title: Telangana HC sets aside trial court order, allows realty firm’s plea in land dispute
news.para: Telangana High Court allowed a realty firm's plea, setting aside a trial court's refusal to reject a civil suit. The court found the plaintiffs' case lacked a valid cause of action and was barred by limitation, noting a nearly five-decade delay in filing the suit after multiple property transactions.

news.title: Colliers India's chairman and managing director resigns
news.para: Sankey Prasad has announced his departure as Chairman and Managing Director of Colliers India and Colliers Project Leaders Middle East. He aims to pivot toward entrepreneurial projects and will offer strategic advisory services to clients across India and the MENA region.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body collects over ₹500 crore property tax in seven months; eyes ₹1,000 crore in year
news.para: Navi Mumbai is celebrating a huge win as the Municipal Corporation marks the collection of over Rs 500 crore in property tax within the initial seven months of the fiscal year. The transformation to digital payments has been pivotal, accounting for over Rs 313 crore of the total.

news.title: Maharashtra finalises policy to promote use of artificial sand in construction
news.para: The Maharashtra government has crafted a comprehensive policy advocating the use of artificial sand. District collectors have received an official mandate for swift action, marking a pivotal shift from reliance on natural sand, which is vital for preserving our ecosystems.
